The paper focuses on unsupervised domain adaptation for Machine Reading Comprehension (MRC), which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an Adversarial Domain Adaptation framework, which involves adversarial learning, a popular technique in deep learning and machine learning. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of pre-trained large-scale language models such as ELMo and BERT, which are popular in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the prediction of which domain a given passage-question pair comes from, which is related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper may also be related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) since MRC involves understanding and processing textual information.
